    p Relay.md values the privacy of its users and is committed to complying with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). We collect and process personal data only to the extent necessary to provide the service reliably.
    p For users, we collect the following personal data:
    ul.ml-5
     li Username
     li Name
     li Email address
     li Profile picture
    p This data is used to create and manage user accounts, authenticate users, and provide support. We also store the access times for individual documents to improve our service performance and identify potential security issues.
    p Documents uploaded to Relay.md are stored on our servers until they are deleted by the user or the team owner. This data is used to deliver the documents to the specified destinations as requested by the uploading user. We do not share user data with third parties without the user's explicit consent.
    p Relay.md implements appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect user data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, destruction, or other unlawful processing. These measures are subject to regular review and updates to ensure their effectiveness.
    p Users have the following rights regarding their personal data:
    ul.ml-5
     li Access: Users have the right to access their personal data and to receive a copy of it.
     li Rectification: Users have the right to request that their personal data be rectified if it is inaccurate or incomplete.
     li Erasure: Users have the right to request that their personal data be erased if it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected.
     li Portability: Users have the right to receive their personal data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format and to transmit it to another controller.
    p Users can exercise these rights by contacting us at info@relay.md

